    "body": "Problem:\r\n- Small error in port of v9.1.0678, causing :ball to check w_locked for the wrong window.\r\n- After #27439, free_all_mem() may not wipe out buffers that were open in more than one window before windows were freed.\r\n\r\nSolution:\r\n- Check win_locked() for wp in ex_buffer_all(), not curwin.\r\n- Set b_nwindows to 0 in free_all_mem() before calling close_buffer().\r\n\r\nRef: https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/38473#issuecomment-4125117681 No need to block these fixes on that.\r\n\r\nfree_all_mem() change also looks like it fixed the \"N lua references were leaked!\" warnings on the CI in that PR.",
    "closed_at": "2026-03-25T10:47:13Z",
    "comment_data": [],
    "comment_regular_data": [
